Version: 0.1.12
Date: 2026-04-12

Changes:
- Guidance filename strategy upgraded for lower collision risk:
  `MERLION.md` is now the primary map file, while existing `AGENTS.md`
  remains fully compatible for loading and maintenance workflows.
- Path-guided map bootstrap behavior fixed:
  map generation no longer short-circuits when any nested guidance file exists.
  Merlion now fills missing guidance per target directory, so root guidance and
  generated subdirectory maps can coexist.
- Generated fallback maps now default to `.merlion/maps/**/MERLION.md`.
- Session storage localized by default:
  transcripts and usage logs now write to `<project>/.merlion/sessions`.
  Resume remains backward-compatible with legacy global session storage under
  `~/.merlion/projects/<hash>` when no local session match is found.
- Agents maintenance scripts (`update`/`lint`) now support both `MERLION.md`
  and `AGENTS.md` guidance files.
- Documentation updates:
  README and feature specs updated to reflect guidance-file compatibility,
  map-generation behavior, and local session defaults.

Related commits:
- feat(runtime): phase milestones, map refresh, and code index hygiene
- feat(context): MERLION.md guidance compatibility + local session storage defaults
